                  Another Note is this;
                  Obſerv. That there are no priviledges or dignities of
men that can ſecure them from Gods ſtroke.

But now that all may be ſealed up unto you, and ſo that we may cloſe the point, know that God will be ſanctified in thoſe that
•• draw nigh to him •
And there are theſe Two things in the Point;

Firſt, For a man to be ſuffered to proſper in a ſinful courſe;
For God to let men go on and have their hearts deſire ſatisfied
in an ungodly way.

1 That whoſoever was to pertake of this muſt be holy himſelf;
none can ſanctifie God, but he muſt have a ſanctified heart
himſelfe.

Secondly, this Ordinance it muſt be received in a holy Communion;
There muſt be a Communion of Saints for this Ordinance;
and it cannot be received anywhere elſe but in a Communion
of Saints.

